Diagnosis.
P. perdecorum
sp. nov. (described below) has four facet rows in the eye bridge, flagellomeres 12 and 13 are irregularly cut (
Fig. 35
), the hair patch on the anepisternum is almost oval (Fig. 27 ), the wings (
Fig. 37
) are infuscated among the Sc, and the base of R 1 and C, the medial fork is conspicuously incomplete in contrast to the radial fork, R 2 is strengthened in the middle, the gonapophyses are conspicuously and irregularly wrinkled by many folds (
Figs. 42–44
), the parameres are clearly bent from the lateral view (
Fig. 43
), the hypandrium (
Fig. 42
) has two conspicuous unsclerotized cavities on both sides, and the terminal radiating network of retinaculi is missing (Figs. 32, 41 ).
